article.description: Ryan Granger kicked a 30-yard field goal to end the game and give Coastal Carolina a 23-20 victory over Monmouth on Saturday.
article.headline: Coastal Carolina 7-0 after 23-20 victory over Monmouth
article.linkText: Coastal Carolina 7-0 after 23-20 victory over Monmouth
article.story: WEST LONG BEACH, N.J. -- Ryan Granger kicked a 30-yard field goal to end the game and give Coastal Carolina a 23-20 victory over Monmouth on Saturday. De'Angelo Henderson ran for 91 yards with a score to extend his touchdown streak to an FCS record 21-straight games. Alex Ross was 20 of 31 for 282 yards passing and ran for a score for Coastal Carolina (7-0, 2-0 Big South). Granger also made field goals of 30 and 32 yards. Lavon Chaney ran for 196 yards with two touchdowns, and caught a touchdown pass to lead Monmouth (3-5, 1-2). Cody Williams was 18 of 30 for 207 yards passing with a 17-yard scoring strike to Chaney. Chaney scored on a 21-yard run to tie it at 20 with 24 seconds left in the third quarter. Ross completed four passes, including a 17-yarder on third-and-11, on the Chanticleers final drive to set up Granger's game-winning kick.
